WEBVTT

00:03.604 --> 00:06.540
[ Edvard Grieg's
"Morning Mood" plays ]

00:15.249 --> 00:18.252
[ Snoring ]

00:26.460 --> 00:27.361
[ Alarm beeps ]

00:27.395 --> 00:28.762
Look, Dad.
I'm helping.

00:28.796 --> 00:30.064
Oh, boy. Thank you.

00:30.098 --> 00:32.766
What very exciting help.

00:32.800 --> 00:33.667
What? What?

00:33.701 --> 00:35.569
Dora...
I'm pretending to be political

00:35.603 --> 00:36.704
to get out
of a Spanish test.

00:36.737 --> 00:37.838
Sure, of course.
Like you do.

00:37.871 --> 00:39.407
Come on, Andy.
You're gonna be late.

00:39.440 --> 00:41.842
If you let me go to online
school like I suggested,

00:41.875 --> 00:43.244
I'd already be there!
[ Cellphone rings ]

00:43.277 --> 00:44.312
Mm-hmm.
Your shirt's inside out,

00:44.345 --> 00:45.546
and you might want to do
something about that hair.

00:45.579 --> 00:48.316
Cooper Contracting.
Hey, Ron.

00:48.349 --> 00:50.684
Uh-huh. Today?
Hold on.

00:50.718 --> 00:51.652
Andy, no!

00:51.685 --> 00:55.389
Uh, it's a little tricky
'cause I got the kids,

00:55.423 --> 00:58.192
but, uh...

00:58.226 --> 00:59.793
You know what?
I'll make it work.

00:59.827 --> 01:01.295
I'll see you at 3:00.

01:01.329 --> 01:04.298
Okay.
[ Bunny gasps ]

01:04.332 --> 01:05.433
Okay, scoop it up.

01:05.466 --> 01:07.301
It's still good.
Let's eat.

01:07.335 --> 01:09.470
Woman:
Root your leg into the ground.

01:09.503 --> 01:13.507
Extend your arm branches
into the sky.

01:13.541 --> 01:16.177
[ Exhales ]

01:16.210 --> 01:18.412
Oh!

01:18.446 --> 01:20.848
So, I got a last-minute
inspection this afternoon.

01:20.881 --> 01:23.817
I hate to be Mr. Bummer, but
since your mom's out of town,

01:23.851 --> 01:26.887
you two will have
to take the bus home.

01:26.920 --> 01:27.855
Don't worry, Dad.
We'll make it work.

01:27.888 --> 01:28.789
Once Andy
gets his license,

01:28.822 --> 01:30.558
the bus thing'll be
a thing of the past.

01:30.591 --> 01:32.326
And, Bunny, I'll call
your favorite babysitter, Jenny,

01:32.360 --> 01:34.462
and have her pick you up
from dance class.
She can't.

01:34.495 --> 01:35.296
She had to go to Cancun,

01:35.329 --> 01:36.764
'cause her Grandma died.
Wink, wink.

01:36.797 --> 01:37.631
Good to know.

01:37.665 --> 01:40.668
Okay, I'll call Magda.
She's in Poland.

01:40.701 --> 01:43.771
Her sister's getting married,
but it's a big mistake.

01:43.804 --> 01:45.206
You have very interesting
conversations

01:45.239 --> 01:46.474
with your baby-sitters.

01:46.507 --> 01:48.476
All right. I'll call...
Let's see.

01:48.509 --> 01:49.210
I'll call...

01:49.243 --> 01:51.479
What about Alice?

01:51.512 --> 01:54.248
Yeah.
What about Alice?

01:54.282 --> 01:55.416
Um...

01:55.449 --> 01:56.850
Oh, is that, like,
uncomfortable?

01:56.884 --> 01:57.851
Like, asking her
to pick up your kid?

01:57.885 --> 01:59.753
Honestly, it doesn't
really seem like her thing.

01:59.787 --> 02:00.554
Uh...

02:00.588 --> 02:02.690
The last time you uhh-ed
like that

02:02.723 --> 02:04.758
was when I asked
if you've smoked pot before.

02:04.792 --> 02:06.727
Oh, what was the answer,
by the way?

02:06.760 --> 02:09.197
Uhh...
You know what, Bunny?

02:09.230 --> 02:10.298
I will ask Alice.

02:10.331 --> 02:11.299
Because it's totally
not a big deal

02:11.332 --> 02:13.767
in any way, shape, or form.
[ Doorbell rings ]

02:13.801 --> 02:15.636
This may seem like a big deal
in some way, shape, or form,

02:15.669 --> 02:18.839
but it's totally not.
He wants a kidney.
I knew it.

02:18.872 --> 02:21.209
Could you pick up Bunny
from dance class today
and drive her home?

02:21.242 --> 02:23.811
This is worse!
Give him a kidney!

02:23.844 --> 02:25.646
Mary: This is Alice.
When she was a kid,

02:25.679 --> 02:27.648
she dreamed up me
to be her BFF.

02:27.681 --> 02:29.917
Now my girl
has finally fallen in love,

02:29.950 --> 02:32.820
but she's in way over her head.
So I'm back to help!

02:32.853 --> 02:34.488
I've got this
all figured out.

02:34.522 --> 02:35.723
No, you don't.

02:35.756 --> 02:37.858
No, I don't.

02:37.891 --> 02:39.560
Pick up Bunny
from dance class?

02:39.593 --> 02:41.362
No, we can't.
Thank you. Goodbye.

02:41.395 --> 02:42.263
I'll be home right after.

02:42.296 --> 02:43.664
I just have a work thing
that popped up.

02:43.697 --> 02:45.299
Not our problem,
Mr. Mom.

02:45.333 --> 02:48.202
Uh...let me
check my schedule.

02:48.236 --> 02:50.238
You know, if it's inconvenient,
you could just say so.

02:50.271 --> 02:52.406
If you pick up the child
of a man you are dating,

02:52.440 --> 02:53.807
you are breaking
the mom seal.

02:53.841 --> 02:54.708
What?

02:54.742 --> 02:56.710
Oh, I-I just said,
if it's inconvenient...

02:56.744 --> 02:57.478
Yup! Sure, sure.

02:57.511 --> 02:59.380
If you do
this one mom thing,

02:59.413 --> 03:01.782
then it's gonna be all
mom things all the time.

03:01.815 --> 03:02.883
I promise, it's just
a one-time thing.

03:02.916 --> 03:04.952
And if you're going to pretend
to check your calendar,

03:04.985 --> 03:06.820
at least
open the app, rookie.

03:06.854 --> 03:08.322
Look, I know
it's a huge favor,

03:08.356 --> 03:10.324
but you'd really
be saving me.

03:10.358 --> 03:13.227
I'll give you a foot massage
and snuggles.

03:13.261 --> 03:15.263
Well, I had a foot massage
and snuggles

03:15.296 --> 03:16.430
scheduled
for this afternoon,

03:16.464 --> 03:18.599
but I'll cancel it.
I'm in.

03:18.632 --> 03:19.333
Really?

03:19.367 --> 03:20.301
Really.
Really?

03:20.334 --> 03:21.168
Amazing! Oh, my God.

03:21.201 --> 03:22.836
Thank you so much!
This is so great.

03:22.870 --> 03:25.273
It's no big deal.
I've given people rides before.

03:25.306 --> 03:27.408
This is just a ride
for a smaller person.

03:27.441 --> 03:28.642
Exactly.
So it'll be cake.

03:28.676 --> 03:30.378
Mad cake.
Calm down.

03:30.411 --> 03:31.945
Oh, and, Alice,
don't worry.

03:31.979 --> 03:32.646
I'm not.

03:32.680 --> 03:33.314
I'll call
the dance studio

03:33.347 --> 03:34.114
and tell them
you're coming

03:34.147 --> 03:35.316
so they know
you aren't a kidnapper,

03:35.349 --> 03:37.551
but could you just fax them
a copy of your driver's license

03:37.585 --> 03:38.452
and proof of insurance?

03:38.486 --> 03:40.254
Bunny should be happy,
but if she's grumpy,

03:40.288 --> 03:41.389
just play Radio Disney.

03:41.422 --> 03:43.657
And bring a snack,
but no nuts.

03:43.691 --> 03:45.493
Well, you can bring peanuts,
just not tree nuts,

03:45.526 --> 03:46.927
not after the incident.
Okay, slow down.

03:46.960 --> 03:48.396
Don't worry.
You're gonna be fine.

03:48.429 --> 03:49.630
I love you. Bye.

03:49.663 --> 03:51.899
Oh, and don't worry,
she has her booster.

03:51.932 --> 03:53.867
[ Whispering ]
What's a booster?

03:53.901 --> 03:55.736
Part of
a spaceship, duh!

03:55.769 --> 03:58.005
[ Sighs ]

03:58.038 --> 03:59.940
We're gonna need help.

03:59.973 --> 04:02.610
Okay, we have a major
situation on our hands.

04:02.643 --> 04:03.611
Okay, before
you get all mad,

04:03.644 --> 04:05.346
what is the point
of doing PR for pro athletes

04:05.379 --> 04:06.013
if we can't date them?

04:06.046 --> 04:07.881
Preach!

04:07.915 --> 04:09.783
I have to pick up
Ben's youngest daughter

04:09.817 --> 04:11.051
from ballet class,
and I need you

04:11.084 --> 04:12.886
to tell me how to do that.
Go.

04:12.920 --> 04:14.822
Bring some juice.
Kids like juice.

04:14.855 --> 04:17.758
Maybe, like, an iPad.
Two iPads.

04:17.791 --> 04:20.794
Frisbee. When I was a kid,
I loved Frisbee.

04:20.828 --> 04:24.031
Do any of you
actually have children?

04:24.064 --> 04:26.367
Ew.

04:26.400 --> 04:27.635
Who has children?!

04:27.668 --> 04:28.969
There's a lady
in accounting

04:29.002 --> 04:30.738
who seems like she's doing
the best she can.

04:32.373 --> 04:35.643
A booster is a portable
car seat for young kids.

04:35.676 --> 04:38.346
Slash part of a spaceship.
Agree to disagree.

04:38.379 --> 04:39.613
You put it
in your backseat.

04:39.647 --> 04:40.914
You put it
in your backseat!

04:40.948 --> 04:41.882
I do not like
this lady.

04:41.915 --> 04:43.851
[ Clears throat ]
Definitely bring a snack.

04:43.884 --> 04:45.786
Nothing you ate
when you were a child.

04:45.819 --> 04:46.887
It all causes cancer.

04:46.920 --> 04:49.790
Something that you
would eat today.
Spicy tuna.

04:49.823 --> 04:51.825
Regular tuna?
Hand roll? Cut roll?

04:51.859 --> 04:53.527
Just tell me
what to bring.

04:53.561 --> 04:54.495
Carrots.

04:54.528 --> 04:56.797
I was just
about to say that.

04:56.830 --> 04:58.566
"Car-rots."

04:58.599 --> 05:00.501
Megan, you are
a lifesaver.

05:00.534 --> 05:02.069
I cannot thank you enough.

05:03.937 --> 05:07.040
**

05:08.108 --> 05:09.843
[ Brakes squeal ]

05:11.712 --> 05:13.814
[ Sighs ]
Later, Davrosh.

05:13.847 --> 05:15.683
Thank you for the mints
and tiny waters.

05:15.716 --> 05:17.551
Five stars for sure.

05:17.585 --> 05:18.952
Ben:
Um, Andy, Dora?

05:18.986 --> 05:21.655
That's an unusual bus.
Dad, don't be mad.

05:21.689 --> 05:23.090
You said we could
take Uber home from school

05:23.123 --> 05:25.025
if we ever
really needed to.

05:25.058 --> 05:26.560
And today,
we really needed to.

05:26.594 --> 05:28.829
This is a loose interpretation
of "really needed to."

05:28.862 --> 05:29.830
What's wrong with the bus?

05:29.863 --> 05:31.665
Uh, well, for starters,

05:31.699 --> 05:33.967
the driver-to-passenger
ratio is outrageous.

05:34.001 --> 05:35.503
Dad, the bus stop is,
like, a block away.

05:35.536 --> 05:36.303
Who has the time?

05:36.336 --> 05:38.806
Okay, new rule --
No more Ubers.

05:38.839 --> 05:40.441
[ Scoffs ] How are we
supposed to get anywhere?

05:40.474 --> 05:42.843
Simple. Andy will
get his driver's license.

05:42.876 --> 05:43.711
Enough putting it off.

05:43.744 --> 05:45.112
All you have left
is the road test.

05:45.145 --> 05:46.847
Mnh, uh, no,
I'm good.

05:46.880 --> 05:48.115
Come on!
When I was your age,

05:48.148 --> 05:49.683
I was dying
to get my license.

05:49.717 --> 05:51.018
I could finally drive
myself to the movies.

05:51.051 --> 05:51.985
Netflix.

05:52.019 --> 05:53.086
The mall.
Amazon.

05:53.120 --> 05:54.588
The record store.
Both: Spotify,

05:54.622 --> 05:56.424
Apple Music, Tidal.

05:56.457 --> 05:57.391
I'm starting to
understand a lot more

05:57.425 --> 05:58.325
about my credit card bill.

05:58.358 --> 06:00.761
Dad, everyone knows
that, in five years,

06:00.794 --> 06:02.563
cars will be
driving themselves.

06:02.596 --> 06:04.865
Okay, but for now,
let's get your license,

06:04.898 --> 06:06.534
and then in five years,
we'll reassess.

06:06.567 --> 06:07.868
I'm making you
an appointment at the DMV.

06:07.901 --> 06:10.904
I don't want my license.
You will drive, Andy!

06:10.938 --> 06:12.906
Never!
Oh, you won't be saying that
when I buy you a car.

06:12.940 --> 06:14.808
I'll reject that car.
Oh, really?

06:14.842 --> 06:16.143
You're gonna reject
an entry-level offering

06:16.176 --> 06:16.944
from a luxury brand?

06:16.977 --> 06:18.746
I don't care
how luxurious it is,

06:18.779 --> 06:19.747
I will never
get in it.

06:19.780 --> 06:21.682
I'm getting you a car,
and you're gonna drive it.

06:21.715 --> 06:22.983
And you're gonna feel
the wind in your hair.

06:23.016 --> 06:24.685
I'll shave my head.
And the sun on your back.

06:24.718 --> 06:25.953
I'll wear
a turtleneck sweater!

06:25.986 --> 06:26.987
And the freedom
of the open road.

06:27.020 --> 06:29.557
Ah --
And that is final!

06:29.590 --> 06:32.125
Now give me a kiss.

06:32.159 --> 06:33.727
Andy?

06:33.761 --> 06:35.429
I love you.

06:37.665 --> 06:39.166
Wow.
The auto industry's

06:39.199 --> 06:41.435
got their hooks in him
pretty deep.

06:41.469 --> 06:44.838
[ Engine shuts off ]
Oh, why am I so nervous?

06:44.872 --> 06:46.540
All I'm doing is
picking up a child

06:46.574 --> 06:47.908
and putting her
in the car.

06:47.941 --> 06:50.511
Kidnappers do it every day!
How hard can it be?

06:50.544 --> 06:53.481
We can still drive away.
"Thelma & Louise" it.

06:53.514 --> 06:54.515
Ooh, I'm Susan Sarandon!

06:54.548 --> 06:56.784
They both die.
Huh. Never saw it.

06:56.817 --> 06:58.552
Besides,
I made a promise.

06:58.586 --> 07:01.622
Fine! If your heart
is set on this,

07:01.655 --> 07:03.791
you know what we need.

07:03.824 --> 07:06.226
Do it!
Uh-huh.

07:06.259 --> 07:08.028
[ Alicia Keys' "Girl on Fire"
playing ]

07:08.061 --> 07:09.463
Now, this is how
we get psyched.

07:09.497 --> 07:12.500
All right. Okay.
* She got both feet
on the ground *

07:12.533 --> 07:14.034
I'm feeling it.
Damn right you are!

07:14.067 --> 07:15.836
Now, tell me --
Who made the hot list

07:15.869 --> 07:17.705
of best PR executives
when she was 27?

07:17.738 --> 07:18.539
That's me.

07:18.572 --> 07:20.073
Who was asked to prom
as a freshman?

07:20.107 --> 07:21.174
C'est moi.

07:21.208 --> 07:23.210
And who won their sixth grade
spelling bee by a mile?

07:23.243 --> 07:23.977
Steve Cribbs.

07:24.011 --> 07:25.779
But who came
in a distant second

07:25.813 --> 07:27.080
without studying
like a nerd?

07:27.114 --> 07:28.716
I did!

07:28.749 --> 07:32.486
Both:
* This girl is on fire!

07:32.520 --> 07:33.353
Whoo!

07:33.386 --> 07:38.926
[ Muffled ]
* This girl is on fire

07:38.959 --> 07:41.562
You can do anything.
You're smart. You're hot.

07:41.595 --> 07:44.965
Now let's go get
what's-her-face from ballet!

07:44.998 --> 07:48.602
Be cool, act nonchalant.
You do this all the time.

07:48.636 --> 07:50.971
That was a tad
on the nose.

07:51.004 --> 07:53.774
Alice!
Bunny!

07:53.807 --> 07:55.976
How was class?
Good. I'm hungry.

07:56.009 --> 07:58.045
Kale chips, apple
slices, or yogurt?

07:58.078 --> 07:59.647
Apples.

07:59.680 --> 08:01.114
What?!
And I'm cold.

08:01.148 --> 08:02.883
Oh.

08:02.916 --> 08:05.118
Yes!
And I'm thirsty.

08:05.152 --> 08:08.255
Mary: Nice!
And bored.

08:08.288 --> 08:09.923
Boom!
You are nailing this!

08:09.957 --> 08:12.125
Woman:
I thought I had them.
Girl: Mom!

08:12.159 --> 08:14.094
Do you need snacks?
We have extra.

08:14.127 --> 08:14.995
Thank you.

08:15.028 --> 08:17.731
I'm over-prepared
and super experienced.

08:17.765 --> 08:20.868
[ Whispering ]
Okay, Bunny, let's roll.

08:20.901 --> 08:22.836
Why were we so scared of
breaking the mom seal?

08:22.870 --> 08:24.237
This is mad cake.

08:24.271 --> 08:26.574
You know what?
Let's not go home right away.

08:26.607 --> 08:27.875
Maybe we should
get some fro yo.

08:27.908 --> 08:28.408
What do you think?

08:28.441 --> 08:29.142
Yeah --
[ Thuds ]

08:29.176 --> 08:31.244
[ Gasps ]

08:31.278 --> 08:33.280
Oh, no.
Holy crap, you broke it!

08:33.313 --> 08:34.214
Are you okay?

08:34.247 --> 08:35.949
I hit my head.
It hurts.

08:35.983 --> 08:38.085
Oh! It's okay. We got this.
Wipe your prints and run!

08:38.118 --> 08:39.052
Okay, Bunny,
it's okay.

08:39.086 --> 08:41.021
I know what to do
because I am a grown-up,

08:41.054 --> 08:42.790
and grown-ups
know what to do, okay?

08:42.823 --> 08:43.824
So let's do it.

08:43.857 --> 08:46.126
[ Tires screech ]

08:46.159 --> 08:48.629
Can't this thing
go any faster?

08:48.662 --> 08:50.631
Uh, ma'am,
I think she's okay.

08:50.664 --> 08:51.464
I made a rooster.

08:51.498 --> 08:52.900
Listen, mister,
when you have kids,

08:52.933 --> 08:54.334
you can tell me
how much to worry, okay?

08:54.367 --> 08:55.636
I have six kids.

08:55.669 --> 08:56.970
Well, aren't you fertile!

08:57.004 --> 08:58.806
And congrats.
That's a lot of kids.

08:58.839 --> 08:59.873
But I work with athletes,

08:59.907 --> 09:02.142
and you can never tell
how serious a concussion is.

09:02.175 --> 09:05.012
She could be bleeding to death
inside her head right now!

09:05.045 --> 09:06.246
But you're not.
Honey, you're gonna be fine.

09:06.279 --> 09:08.115
Your daddy's gonna meet us
at the hospital.

09:08.148 --> 09:10.050
[ Whispering ]
For brain surgery.

09:10.083 --> 09:11.852
[ Normal voice ]
God, step on it,

09:11.885 --> 09:12.953
and give me some siren!

09:12.986 --> 09:14.755
[ Siren wailing ]

09:14.788 --> 09:15.623
Ben:
All right.

09:15.656 --> 09:17.758
Seat belt's fastened,
mirror's checked.

09:17.791 --> 09:21.094
Now start the car.

09:21.128 --> 09:23.330
Should we check traffic
and weather together on the 8s?

09:23.363 --> 09:25.265
Andy, just start the car.

09:25.298 --> 09:27.134
You need
the practice, bud.

09:27.167 --> 09:28.836
Okay, here I go.

09:28.869 --> 09:30.704
Pulling out into
possible gridlock

09:30.738 --> 09:33.974
and God knows what kind
of weather system.

09:34.007 --> 09:36.677
Dad, I am scared to drive!
What?

09:36.710 --> 09:38.679
Just like I was
to run, bike, and skip.

09:38.712 --> 09:40.080
Why are you
even surprised?

09:40.113 --> 09:41.915
I don't know what
you're saying right now.

09:41.949 --> 09:43.216
I mean, I still think
self-driving cars

09:43.250 --> 09:44.317
will be the way
of the future,

09:44.351 --> 09:46.954
but, for now,
I'm just not ready.

09:46.987 --> 09:50.891
Look, it's okay
to be scared,

09:50.924 --> 09:52.359
but do you think
I'd want you driving

09:52.392 --> 09:54.327
if I didn't think
you were ready?

09:54.361 --> 09:57.330
Come on.
You got this.
[ Pats knee ]

09:57.364 --> 09:59.700
Hit it.
[ Cellphone chimes ]

09:59.733 --> 10:01.234
Okay.
Stop the car.

10:01.268 --> 10:02.369
Bunny's at
the hospital.

10:02.402 --> 10:04.004
Oh, thank God!
I mean, is she okay?

10:04.037 --> 10:07.274
[ Quietly ]
Oh, thank you, God.

10:10.143 --> 10:12.379
Daddy!
Oh, hey, sweetie.

10:12.412 --> 10:13.781
Are you feeling okay?

10:13.814 --> 10:15.282
Yeah, I had
the best day ever!

10:15.315 --> 10:16.316
[ Chuckles ]

10:16.349 --> 10:18.385
Mr. Cooper, as you can see,
your daughter's fine.

10:18.418 --> 10:21.254
Your girlfriend, however,
was pretty riled up.

10:21.288 --> 10:24.191
We gave her
a sedative.

10:24.224 --> 10:25.859
Thank you.

10:27.194 --> 10:28.796
[ Grunts ]

10:32.800 --> 10:34.802
Hey.

10:34.835 --> 10:37.104
Why am I here?

10:37.137 --> 10:38.872
Please take me
to my apartment

10:38.906 --> 10:41.241
where I can die of shame
in peace.

10:41.274 --> 10:43.343
Come on.
So you overreacted.

10:43.376 --> 10:44.511
You're new at this.

10:44.544 --> 10:47.180
When Andy was a baby,
I thought every sneeze was T.B.

10:47.214 --> 10:48.782
Your reaction falls
into a category

10:48.816 --> 10:50.150
I would call "normal plus."

10:50.183 --> 10:52.119
"Normal plus"?
Yeah.

10:52.152 --> 10:53.186
Normal,
plus what you did.

10:53.220 --> 10:54.054
[ Scoffs ]

10:54.087 --> 10:56.757
Trust me,
next time, you'll be better.

10:56.790 --> 10:58.025
Homie say next time?

10:58.058 --> 10:59.960
You just got to
get back on the horse.

10:59.993 --> 11:01.862
What do you think about
picking up Bunny again tomorrow?

11:01.895 --> 11:05.298
Homie say tomorrow?
Pretending I agree
with your reasoning,

11:05.332 --> 11:07.034
tomorrow seems soon.

11:07.067 --> 11:08.301
Honey, you're gonna
be great.

11:08.335 --> 11:10.704
So you messed up.
It's not gonna happen again.

11:10.738 --> 11:12.940
The Titanic
didn't sink twice.

11:12.973 --> 11:14.742
[ Smooches ]

11:14.775 --> 11:18.779
That's because it was
at the bottom of the ocean.

11:18.812 --> 11:20.748
Hey, boss lady.
Reminder --

11:20.781 --> 11:23.450
You have "Scary, scary
ballet time" at 3:30.

11:23.483 --> 11:25.052
I think I saw them
at Coachella.

11:25.085 --> 11:27.187
It's not a band.
It's an errand I'm dreading.

11:27.220 --> 11:29.056
Pretty sure it's a band,
pretty sure my cousin's in it,

11:29.089 --> 11:30.023
pretty sure
they swept the VMAs.

11:30.057 --> 11:32.259
Anyway, this skinny kid
is here to see you.

11:32.292 --> 11:34.194
Andy: I prefer
skinny young adult.

11:34.227 --> 11:36.163
Andy. Hi.

11:36.196 --> 11:37.330
Is everything okay?

11:37.364 --> 11:38.298
Yes, yes. Well, no.

11:38.331 --> 11:40.801
No, Alice, it's not,
and thank you for asking.

11:40.834 --> 11:43.370
I need to talk to an adult
who's not my dad but knows him.

11:43.403 --> 11:45.405
I didn't have your number,
but it was very easy for me

11:45.438 --> 11:47.207
to find
your work address online.
Yeah.

11:47.240 --> 11:48.776
Along with a rumor
you dated A-Rod.

11:49.943 --> 11:51.078
How can I help you?

11:51.111 --> 11:52.846
It's Ben.
Uh-huh.

11:52.880 --> 11:53.847
My dad.
Yes.

11:53.881 --> 11:56.283
He wants me to get
my driver's license so bad

11:56.316 --> 11:58.786
he even threatened
to buy me my own car.

11:58.819 --> 11:59.519
It's horrible.

11:59.552 --> 12:01.088
Why don't you
want to drive?

12:01.121 --> 12:03.991
Because I'm scared.
I am afraid to drive.

12:04.024 --> 12:06.293
You know me --
I am a mess!

12:06.326 --> 12:08.796
I-In what world
does it make sense

12:08.829 --> 12:11.064
for me to get behind
the wheel of a car?

12:11.098 --> 12:12.966
I mean,
what if I hurt someone?

12:13.000 --> 12:15.302
That I get.

12:15.335 --> 12:16.804
You know what
you should do

12:16.837 --> 12:17.938
if you're afraid to drive?

12:17.971 --> 12:19.406
Not drive.

12:19.439 --> 12:21.141
I've been thinking
about this a lot lately,

12:21.174 --> 12:23.076
and I don't think anyone
should have to do anything

12:23.110 --> 12:24.812
that they are
afraid to do.

12:24.845 --> 12:25.979
Really?
Yes.

12:26.013 --> 12:28.281
Fear is your body's way of
telling you not to do something.

12:28.315 --> 12:30.083
If you're afraid to drive,
just walk.

12:30.117 --> 12:33.086
Or jog
if you're in a hurry.

12:33.120 --> 12:35.055
Thank you.
Thank you.

12:35.088 --> 12:38.458
That is exactly the wonderful
advice I wanted to hear.

12:38.491 --> 12:39.993
You know,
I'm gonna go home.

12:40.027 --> 12:41.995
I'm gonna say,
"Hey, Dad...[pounds table]

12:42.029 --> 12:43.463
I am a walker."

12:43.496 --> 12:47.234
If you ever need anything,
I owe you big time.

12:47.267 --> 12:49.402
[ Smooches, blows ]

12:50.137 --> 12:51.939
A-Andy?

12:51.972 --> 12:54.441
I actually could
use a favor.

13:02.215 --> 13:06.586
Andy, what did I say
about taking Uber?

13:06.619 --> 13:07.420
Bunny?

13:07.454 --> 13:09.356
Five stars,
Jasmine!

13:09.389 --> 13:11.191
Hey, Dad.
I have to go potty.

13:11.224 --> 13:13.160
Do not disturb me.

13:13.193 --> 13:15.562
[ Vehicle door closes ]
What is happening
right now?

13:15.595 --> 13:17.030
Dad, I know
what you're thinking.

13:17.064 --> 13:19.032
Don't worry.
I didn't use your Uber account.

13:19.066 --> 13:20.868
Alice let me use hers
to pick up Bunny instead.

13:20.901 --> 13:22.335
Alice?
Why were you with Alice?

13:22.369 --> 13:23.470
Oh, I stopped by her office,

13:23.503 --> 13:25.172
and we had
this long, productive talk,

13:25.205 --> 13:27.040
and she told me that
I should embrace my fear,

13:27.074 --> 13:29.142
so I'm never driving.

13:29.176 --> 13:30.043
U-Um, what?

13:30.077 --> 13:31.478
Fear is my friend, Dad.

13:31.511 --> 13:33.446
Fear is my lover
and my master.

13:33.480 --> 13:35.282
I walk at
my own pace.

13:35.315 --> 13:36.616
Which I will be doing
a lot of

13:36.649 --> 13:38.919
because of what I said
re driving.

13:38.952 --> 13:40.453
Andy, this can't be
what she meant.

13:40.487 --> 13:42.189
Oh, no,
she was extremely clear.

13:42.222 --> 13:44.858
Like the tears I cry
when I think about driving.

13:46.626 --> 13:48.896
You will drive, Andrew!

13:48.929 --> 13:50.230
Ben wants to
come have a talk.

13:50.263 --> 13:51.564
Who comes anywhere
and talks?

13:51.598 --> 13:53.633
Like, just send the rest
in a text, buddy.

13:53.666 --> 13:56.536
Yeah, seriously. I hate when
people want to talk about stuff.

13:56.569 --> 13:58.571
Just bottle it up inside
like the rest of us.

13:58.605 --> 14:00.507
You know it has to do
with me and the kids.

14:00.540 --> 14:02.642
I didn't do anything wrong.
Bunny got home.

14:02.675 --> 14:06.179
In style.
If Ben is asking me
to help with the kids,

14:06.213 --> 14:07.280
he's got to let me
do it my way.

14:07.314 --> 14:08.515
The Alice way.
Exactly.

14:08.548 --> 14:10.550
Yeah, like sending
the kids home in a limo

14:10.583 --> 14:12.619
instead of driving them
around like a lame-ass.

14:12.652 --> 14:14.221
I wouldn't say it
like that, really.

14:14.254 --> 14:15.322
Or telling
a scaredy-cat teen

14:15.355 --> 14:17.925
to embrace his fear
and live life like a pedestrian.

14:17.958 --> 14:19.359
I feel like there
are better examples.

14:19.392 --> 14:21.061
Mm, not really.

14:21.094 --> 14:22.629
Maybe I did mess up.

14:22.662 --> 14:24.497
[ Groaning ]
God, I need a drink.

14:24.531 --> 14:26.666
Now that we agree on.

14:26.699 --> 14:29.236
Nothing soothes
like ice-cold vodka.

14:29.269 --> 14:30.670
That's actually ice cream,

14:30.703 --> 14:32.105
which you are putting
in the microwave.

14:32.139 --> 14:33.173
What's happening?
What's happening?

14:33.206 --> 14:35.042
[ Sighs ] I'm heating up
some mint chocolate chip.

14:35.075 --> 14:36.143
To drink?

14:36.176 --> 14:38.278
It's the only thing
that calms my nerves these days.

14:38.311 --> 14:40.180
I think I've built up
a full immunity to whiskey.

14:40.213 --> 14:42.415
[ Microwave beeps ]

14:47.387 --> 14:48.688
[ Both sigh ]

14:48.721 --> 14:50.590
Oh, yeah.
That's doing the trick.

14:50.623 --> 14:51.491
I told you.

14:51.524 --> 14:53.994
I'm feeling good
in all sorts of places.

14:54.027 --> 14:55.662
[ Doorbell rings ]

14:55.695 --> 14:58.198
[ Groans ]

14:58.231 --> 15:00.133
Hey, babe.

15:00.167 --> 15:02.002
What a wonderful surprise.
Come on in.

15:02.035 --> 15:05.405
I'll heat you up
some mint chocolate chip.

15:05.438 --> 15:08.141
Um, Andy's
under the impression

15:08.175 --> 15:10.010
that you advised him
to be ruled by fear.

15:10.043 --> 15:11.211
This is
a misunderstanding, no?

15:11.244 --> 15:13.346
I never said "ruled."
Okay, Alice...

15:13.380 --> 15:15.415
Okay, I let the conversation
get away from me,

15:15.448 --> 15:16.716
but, yeah, I said
sometimes,

15:16.749 --> 15:19.152
when you are scared
of something,

15:19.186 --> 15:20.120
it's okay to back off.

15:20.153 --> 15:22.322
So that explains why Bunny
was in the Uber.

15:22.355 --> 15:23.323
If you didn't want
to pick her up,

15:23.356 --> 15:24.057
you should have
just told me.

15:24.091 --> 15:25.692
Could I have?
'Cause I tried,

15:25.725 --> 15:27.727
and you told me
to get back on the horse.

15:27.760 --> 15:30.130
Maybe some people
should not ride horses.

15:30.163 --> 15:31.298
What are you trying
to say here?

15:31.331 --> 15:34.534
I'm trying to say
maybe I should

15:34.567 --> 15:35.502
take a step back

15:35.535 --> 15:37.704
on the whole me
helping with the kids thing.

15:39.206 --> 15:40.273
Great.

15:40.307 --> 15:41.508
Because after
today's events,

15:41.541 --> 15:43.343
I was gonna say
the same thing, so...

15:43.376 --> 15:46.313
Great.

15:46.346 --> 15:47.380
Great.

15:52.719 --> 15:57.457
Chug, chug, chug, chug,
chug, chug, chug, chug!

15:57.490 --> 16:00.493
Sure you don't want
to give whiskey another shot?

16:06.133 --> 16:07.700
It's not that I don't want
to help with the kids.

16:07.734 --> 16:10.370
It's just
what if I suck at it?

16:10.403 --> 16:12.339
Is that gonna be
a deal breaker with Ben?

16:12.372 --> 16:13.773
It kind of freaks me out,
you know?

16:13.806 --> 16:15.742
Uh, I don't think you're
supposed to talk during this.

16:15.775 --> 16:17.377
My parents were garbage.

16:17.410 --> 16:19.112
I don't even know
what good parents look like.

16:19.146 --> 16:20.013
That's not true.

16:20.047 --> 16:22.082
You watched "The Cosby Show"
all the time.

16:22.115 --> 16:24.251
There's something
I have to tell you
about him. Later.

16:24.284 --> 16:26.519
Look, if you want to bail
on this whole Ben thing,

16:26.553 --> 16:28.721
my "Thelma & Louise" pitch
is still on the table

16:28.755 --> 16:30.257
in a very real way.

16:30.290 --> 16:32.359
Still no.
Fine.

16:32.392 --> 16:34.794
If you want this to work,
then you got to dive in.

16:34.827 --> 16:37.064
Ben's not asking you
to be perfect --

16:37.097 --> 16:40.767
he's just asking you
to try.

16:40.800 --> 16:42.535
Thanks, Mary.

16:42.569 --> 16:44.437
You should go
talk to Ben.

16:44.471 --> 16:46.573
I should go
talk to Ben.

16:46.606 --> 16:49.776
So what's the deal
with Dr. Huxtable?

16:49.809 --> 16:51.711
[ Slow-tempo music plays ]
[ Door closes ]

16:51.744 --> 16:54.147
Hello?

16:54.181 --> 16:55.248
Hey, Andy.

16:55.282 --> 16:56.249
Where's your dad?

16:56.283 --> 16:57.684
[ Sighs ]
Alice, my friend.

16:57.717 --> 17:00.053
You are a sight
for sore eyes.

17:00.087 --> 17:02.422
What's going on?
Are you okay?

17:02.455 --> 17:04.557
[ Scoffs ]
Not in so many letters.

17:04.591 --> 17:07.427
At first, I thought embracing
my fear was the answer,

17:07.460 --> 17:10.097
but now
I-I'm not so sure.

17:10.130 --> 17:11.698
I feel like --
like...

17:11.731 --> 17:15.702
What's another way of saying
"empty pointless loser"?

17:15.735 --> 17:19.306
Andy, I was wrong.
[ Chuckles ]

17:19.339 --> 17:22.642
You can conquer your fears,
and you should.

17:22.675 --> 17:24.211
But how?

17:24.244 --> 17:26.713
Let's start by changing
the music.

17:26.746 --> 17:29.282
May I?

17:29.316 --> 17:31.184
Okay.
[ Beeps ]

17:31.218 --> 17:35.222
Now, listen to this music
and tell me what you feel.

17:35.255 --> 17:36.723
* She's just a girl,
and she's on fire *

17:36.756 --> 17:40.860
[ Sighs ]
I guess I feel...sad, still.

17:40.893 --> 17:44.097
I mean, a young lady is
evidently being burned alive

17:44.131 --> 17:46.633
and Alicia Keys
is just going on about it.

17:46.666 --> 17:48.168
Um, okay.

17:48.201 --> 17:51.104
Maybe don't take the lyrics
quite so literally.

17:51.138 --> 17:53.340
Oh. Okay, yeah.
Yeah.

17:53.373 --> 17:54.707
* But she knows
she can fly away *

17:54.741 --> 17:55.875
I see what
you're going for here.

17:55.908 --> 17:57.410
It's cool, it's cool.

17:57.444 --> 17:59.612
Yeah?
Feels pretty good, right?

17:59.646 --> 18:01.581
Not gonna lie,
it kind of does.

18:01.614 --> 18:02.882
Feels like
you can do anything, yeah?

18:02.915 --> 18:04.751
Yeah.
It -- It really does.

18:04.784 --> 18:06.353
Like you can conquer
all your fears?

18:06.386 --> 18:07.620
Oh, you bet I can.

18:07.654 --> 18:09.856
Even driving?
You know what?

18:09.889 --> 18:11.391
* ...head in the clouds *

18:11.424 --> 18:12.792
I think I can!
You know you can!

18:12.825 --> 18:14.894
I feel like I could even
drive right now!

18:14.927 --> 18:16.763
You know why?
Because...

18:16.796 --> 18:21.434
Both:
* This girl is on fire!

18:21.468 --> 18:23.736
Dude! You made that left
like a boss!

18:23.770 --> 18:27.174
Yeah, I did.
'Cause this girl is on fire!

18:27.207 --> 18:29.242
I-I mean boy.
I mean me.

18:29.276 --> 18:30.643
Yeah, you know
what I'm saying.

18:30.677 --> 18:32.612
I told you. It's all about
that pump-up song.

18:32.645 --> 18:33.546
Yeah, you were so right.

18:33.580 --> 18:35.582
I really do feel
like I can do anything.

18:35.615 --> 18:38.285
Want to go crush
that driving test?

18:38.318 --> 18:39.886
Let's do it.

18:41.488 --> 18:42.489
Dora:
Hello, Father.

18:42.522 --> 18:44.491
[ Door closes ]

18:44.524 --> 18:46.193
Help yourself.
No, thank you.

18:46.226 --> 18:47.660
Hey, do you feel
like I push you into things

18:47.694 --> 18:49.162
without thinking
about your feelings?

18:49.196 --> 18:50.630
Yeah.
With what?

18:50.663 --> 18:52.665
School.
Besides school.

18:52.699 --> 18:53.666
Doing good in school.

18:53.700 --> 18:55.902
I think it's doing "well"
in school, but...

18:55.935 --> 18:57.404
those are things
parents are supposed to do.

18:57.437 --> 18:58.505
You asked,
I answered.

18:58.538 --> 19:01.441
Mm. But if this is about
the whole Andy driving thing,

19:01.474 --> 19:03.676
Alice came by,
dropped off these cupcakes,

19:03.710 --> 19:04.944
and took him out
for a spin.

19:04.977 --> 19:06.579
Wait. What?

19:06.613 --> 19:08.615
Our Andy?
Our Alice?

19:08.648 --> 19:10.650
Honestly,
they're both yours.

19:10.683 --> 19:11.751
Dad!

19:11.784 --> 19:13.486
Dad.

19:13.520 --> 19:15.655
Guess what I just did.

19:15.688 --> 19:18.291
Shut up.
Is that your driver's license?
Yeah.

19:18.325 --> 19:19.959
Dude! That is huge!
[ Door closes ]

19:19.992 --> 19:21.828
I'm so proud
of you, man.

19:21.861 --> 19:23.796
I knew you could do it.
Me too.

19:23.830 --> 19:25.632
I mean,
after a lot of not knowing.

19:25.665 --> 19:27.934
Come on, dude. Let's take
a selfie with that thing.

19:27.967 --> 19:32.339
It's the only good social media
you've had in years.

19:32.372 --> 19:34.741
I don't want to brag,
but I'm an American hero.

19:34.774 --> 19:36.443
How'd you get him
to drive?

19:36.476 --> 19:39.246
What happened?
I thought you were taking a --

19:41.448 --> 19:43.716
I do want to help
with the kids.

19:43.750 --> 19:44.617
Even if it's scary

19:44.651 --> 19:46.419
and I feel like
I'm gonna screw them up,

19:46.453 --> 19:48.455
because that's
how we'll grow,

19:48.488 --> 19:49.489
you and me.

19:49.522 --> 19:51.458
I think I'm gonna cry
hard tears of joy right now.

19:51.491 --> 19:53.593
Please do not.
[ Laughs ]

19:53.626 --> 19:55.895
Look, I'm sorry
I got judgmental.

19:55.928 --> 19:57.096
Parenting
is a learning curve,

19:57.129 --> 19:59.399
and you need to go
at your own pace
to feel supported.

19:59.432 --> 20:02.602
You know, it's actually
kind of cool with kids.

20:02.635 --> 20:07.574
The lows are low,
but the highs are, like...

20:07.607 --> 20:09.742
some things I used to do
and I don't anymore.

20:09.776 --> 20:11.478
I mean, occasionally,
at a party.

20:11.511 --> 20:13.346
Not all the time.
Not the hard stuff.

20:13.380 --> 20:14.414
And never around
the kids -- That I know.

20:14.447 --> 20:17.016
Not around the kids
and do not sell it to them.

20:17.049 --> 20:19.352
Alice, are you taking me
to dance class?

20:19.386 --> 20:20.253
I'd be happy to.

20:20.287 --> 20:21.354
Uh, thank you, sweetie,

20:21.388 --> 20:22.822
but, actually,
I got this covered.

20:22.855 --> 20:23.690
Andy, come in here

20:23.723 --> 20:25.625
and drive your sister
to dance class!

20:25.658 --> 20:27.960
God, that felt good.
[ Laughs ]

20:30.863 --> 20:34.967
I'm doing it! I am driving!
Andy to the max!

20:35.001 --> 20:36.403
Good job, buddy.

20:36.436 --> 20:38.671
This is freedom.
This is the open road.

20:38.705 --> 20:40.039
The wind in our hair!

20:40.072 --> 20:41.441
Why is
everybody yelling?

20:41.474 --> 20:42.875
'Cause yelling is fun!

20:42.909 --> 20:47.947
All:
* This girl is on fire

20:47.980 --> 20:53.786
* This girl is on fire
[ Bicycle bell dings ]

20:53.820 --> 20:58.291
* She's walking on fire *

20:58.325 --> 20:59.792
* This girl is... *

20:59.826 --> 21:02.862
-- Captions by VITAC --
